model_name: default_example. This should be unique for each model entry
git_url: This should be git url of the model. To clone a particular branch specify in url itself.

model_spec.target_application: This will be the type of application this model targets e.g. Object Detection, Face Detection, etc
model_spec.input_dim: This will be input dimension for images to feed the network e.g. 224x224, 64x64, etc.
model_spec.target_network: This can network architecture type e.g. YOLO, squeezeDet, etc.
model_spec.target_framework: This will be the framework used e.g TensorFlow or Keras.
model_spec.target_framework_version: This will be the version used for target framework.
model_spec.dataset_type: This will be type of dataset used for model training
model_spec.other_param: This will be extra param to differentiate same Model but different version

sections._comment: Here User can define multiple sections like training, freeze, tensorboard, evaluation and many more.

example_section._comment: Section name should unique for one model. Section contains information that how to run the section. Section has mainly three type of parameters, command, execution_script and other_parameters.

command.run_type: This parameter determines how to run the given file. Ex: python3, shell, tensorboard etc.

execution_script.default: Path to file from model's root directory

other_parameters.default: This contains default value for perticular parameter.
other_parameters.type: This contains type of parameter. Like file, dir, int, str, flag, float
other_parameters.required: true or false based on parameter is required or not.
